* Inheritance vs Composition

* Inheritance vs Composition

- Inheritance breaks encapsulation

- Composition causes boilerplate to proxy all methods

Example:

    type Engine struct{}

    func (e Engine) Start() { ... }
    func (e Engine) Stop()  { ... }

We want `Car` to be able to `Start` and `Stop` too.

